return {
	["Look at him! He cant use a {toilet} properly."] = "Zeby z {latryny} nie umiec skorzystac, joki cep!",
	["Anyway, soon we'll set out on a further journey. But perhaps, first, would you like to hear the prophecy about the legendary {neyghboor}?"] = "Tak, czy srak, niedlugo wyruszamy w dalsza wedrowke. Ale moze, najpierw chcialbys uslyszec przepowiednie o legendarnynm {somsiedzie}.",
	["...a specific scent not only woke up the companions of adventure but also woke up the vile neyghbor's cravings... Jan Kockodan gets annoyed when someone has it better than him. And he said this: 'This scent is everywhere. It's that dumbass Bilbo, a moron who can afford the hallway paneling. AFTER HIM!! Ugly mutts, run! Follow the scent of wealth!"] = "...specyficzny zapach lobudzil nie tylko towarzyszy przygodowych. Lobudzil tez zadze, lobrzydliwe somsiedzkie zadze... ...Jan Kockodan dostaje smergla, gdy ktos ma lepiej od niego hej. A mowil on tak: Wszedzie poznom ten zapach. Toz to dupsko Bylbe, kurdopla co go na boazerie w przedpokoju stoc. ZA NIIM!! kundle szkaradne, biegiem za odorem bogactwa.",
	["Those wolves were just spirits I summoned to better illustrate the story. The real Jan Kockodan is much more dangerous. If you want to join us, you must complete one challenge. Let's say you steal rum from these pirates here."] = "Te wilki to byly tylko duchy, ktore przywolalem, zeby lepiej zobrazowac te opowiesc. Prawdziwy Jan Kockodan jest o wiele bardziej niebezpieczny. Jesli chcesz do nas dolaczyc, musisz wykonac jedno wyzwanie. Powiedzmy, ze wykradniesz rum tym tutaj piratom.",
	["You can see them from our current location. Be careful; spirited water is only ordinary pastime, but rum on the other hand... It's their holy grail."] = "Widac ich z naszego aktualnego polozenia. Uwazaj, trunki to dla nich jedyna rozrywka, a rum to swietosc wsrod ich starszyzny.",
	["Mmm, delicious. Alright, comrades, it's time to move. See you on the coast at the western steppes."] = "Mmm pyszniutkie. Dobra, kompania, pora sie zwijac. Widzimy sie na zachodnim brzegu na stepach.",
	["Come back with rum, or there's nothing to talk about."] = "Wroc z rumem, inaczej nie ma o czym rozmawiac.",
	["Sorry we went ahead, but we were bored in that wilderness."] = "Wybacz, ze poszlismy przodem, ale nudzilo nam sie na tamtym odludziu.",
	["Let's head to the private docks of the vampire lords. They receive a daily supply of wine for the nobility. We'll sneak in there unnoticed. No one will figure out few bottles or barrels missing."] = "Udajmy sie do prywatnych dokow wampirzych lordow. Dostaja tam codziennie dostawe wina dla szlachty. Wkradniemy sie tam niepostrzezenie. Nikt sie nie skapnie, ze zniklo im kilka butli.",
	["I have a great idea, but I won't tell you while you are sober. I'm already tipsy, now it's your turn."] = "Mam zajebisty pomysl, ale na trzezwo Ci nie powiem. Ja jestem juz wstawiony, pora na ciebie.",
	["We played ourselves. We'll distract the guard, and you try to escape. If we succeed too, we'll meet up at Gertruda place. If we were tio separate, seek help from her."] = "Tosmy sie wkopali. Odciagniemy uwage straznika, a Ty sproboj uciec. Jezeli nam tez sie uda, to mamy zbita pione z Gertruda. Jezeli sie rozdzielimy, szukaj u niej pomocy.",
	["Good thing you found us. I was starting to worry. No time for chit-chat. We tried to extract information about HF-P/X from the desert nomads. One of them claims to know where to find one of the ancient artifacts. We couldn't negotiate with them - maybe you can. Their settlement is in the north of the desert."] = "Dobrze, ze nas znalazles. Juz zaczynalem sie martwic. Szkoda czasu na gadanine. Probowalismy wydobyc od pustynnych nomadow informacje o HF-P/X. Jeden z nich twierdzi, ze wie gdzie znalezc jeden z pradawnych artefaktow. Nie moglismy sie z nimi dogadac - moze tobie sie uda. Ich osada znajduej sie na polnocy pustyni.",
	["Tourists in such a place are an easy target. I told one of the nomads that we wouldn't renovate their old town. Maybe you can offer him something in exchange for information. Currently, they're camped on one of the rocks in the north."] = "Turysci w takim miejscu to rarytas latwy do zweszenia. Mowilem jednemu z nomadow, ze nie odremontujemy im starowki. Moze Ty zaoferuejsz mu cos w zamian za informacje. Aktualnie rozbici sa na jednej ze skalek na polnocy.",
	["I've heard of underground chocolate chip cookie deposits, but natural bud light formations, never. Are you sure about my truth? Well, okay. Go to the lizard village and try to find at least one bud light. In the meantime, we'll go to the Medusa Tower area. Zwalin wants to meet Marluk sister. Although now I come to think about it, we won't stay there long. Ultimately, we'll meet at Hairycles's."] = "Slyszalem o podziemnych zlozach czekoladowych ciasteczek, ale o naturalnych formacjach harnasi nigdy. Jestes pewnien ze moim prawde? No dobra. Pojdz do wioski jaszczuroludzi i sproboj znalezc chociaz jednego harnasia. My w tym czasie udamy sie w okolice medusa tower. Zwalin chce sie zobaczyc z siostra Marluka. Chociaz jak teraz pomysle, to dlugo tam nie zagoscimy. Ostatecznie spotykamy sie u hairyclesa.",
	["Hairycles provided us with directions to HF-P/X's hideout. But first, we need to do him a favor. If possible, bring us about 2^log(10000) bananas."] = "Hairycles podal nam wskazowki, jak dojsc do kryjowki HF-P/X. Ale najpierw wypadloby sie mu odwdzieczyc. Jezeli to mozliwe, to przynies nam tak ze 2^log(10000) bananow.",
	["Thanks for your help. Now we'll head to the eastern monkey village. Between the Kongo village and the monkey grove there lies a hidden entrance to the ruins of an ancient temple."] = "Dzieki za pomoc. Teraz udamy sie w okolice wschodniej osady malp. Miedzy wioska kongo a malpim gajem jest schowane, wsrod gestej dzungli, zejscie do ruin pradawnej swiatyni.",
	["I need exactly 16 bananas to avoid embarassment in front of Hairycles."] = "Potrzebuje dokladnie 16 bananow, zeby nie wyjsc blado przy Hairyclesie.",
	["I have a feeling that Jan Kockodan got ahead of us. Maybe he's hiding somewhere in this hellish cave. Watch out for him! From the notes given to me by Hairycles, it appears that somewhere in this temple are enchanted doors. The key to opening them is to collect three different magical runes. Fortunately, all the runes are in the temple... if no one has stolen them."] = "Cos czuje, ze Jan Kockodan nas wyprzedzil. Mozliwe, ze zaszyl sie gdzies w tej piekielnej jaskini. Uwazaj na niego! Z notatek danych mi przez Hairyclesa wynika, ze gdzies w tej swiatyni sa zaklete drzwi. Kluczem do ich otwarcia jest zebarnie trzech roznych magicznych run. Na szcescie wszystkie runy sa w swiatyni... o ile nikt ich nie ukradl.",
	["Yes, those are all the needed runes. You can now try to find the enchanted doors I mentioned. Maybe we'll find HF-P/X here."] = "Tak, to wszystkie potrzebne runy. Mozesz teraz sprobowac znalezc zaklete drzwi o ktorych mowilem. Byc moze znajdziemy tu HF-P/X.",
	["Unfortunately, I don't know the exact location of the runes."] = "Niestety, nie wiem nic o dokladnym miejscu polozenia run",
	["Wait! Behind those doors might be HF-P/X! Try not to go too deep until we finish collecting, okay?"] = "Czekaj! Za drzwiami moze kryc sie HF-P/X! Sproboj nie zapuszczac sie za gleboko, poki my nie skonczymy sie zbierac, ok?",
	["Shireajevo, year two thousand fifteen. Or was it {sixteenth}? Hmm, not sure..."] = "Shireajewo, rok dwa tysiace pietnasty. A moze {szesnasty}?  Hmm, nie...",
	["I remember now: it was the Year of Linux. Bambalf came to visit my father, Bilbeus. The wizard, as he entered the main room, said to my father, who was sprawled on the couch: 'Have you heard of an android so rich it sleeps on Passats?' and then sat down next to him. My {father} denied it and with unprecedented curiosity, added that they should sit down. Since they were already sitting, I assumed they wanted to sit over vodka that was there on the table."] = "Juz wiem: to byl rok Linuxa. Bambalf przyszedl w odwiedziny do mojego ojca, Bilbeusza. Czarodziej, przechodzac do glownego pokoju mowil do rozwalonego na kanapie {ojca}: 'slyszales o androidzie tak bogatym, ze spi na passatach?', po czym usiadl obok niego. Ojciec zaprzeczyl i z nietajona ciekawoscia dopowiedzial, ze trzeba usiasc na spokojnie. Z racji iz oboje juz siedzieli, domyslilem sie, ze chcial usiasc przy wodce.",
	["Another time, my father invited Bambalf's hunting buddies. Apparently, they were already familiar with the story, as when the Wizard finally arrived, he didn't have to retell it from the beginning. Bambalf explained to my father that these friends were actually the unknown culprits behind the collapse of the state-owned farms around the Brzezinka Mountain. He also mentioned their sarmatian roots and their supposed inheritance from an android sleeping on Passats. Later, they discussed some work agreement and a plan to take over a legitimate inheritance. I don't remember much of it because I was young and didn't understand all the words. Then they drank vodka, and they set off on a {journey}."] = "Innego razu, moj ojciec pozapraszal kolegow z kola mysliwskiego Bambalfa. Najwidoczniej byli juz wtajemniczeni w historie, gdyz gdy Czarodziej w koncu przyszedl, to nie musial opowiadac tej historii od nowa. Bambalf wytluamczyl ojcu, ze Ci koledzy to tak naprawde nieznani sprawcy upadku PGR-ow naokolo Gory Brzezinki. Dodatkowo wspomnial o ich sramackich korzeniach i domniemanym spadku po androidzie spiacycm na passatach. Pozniej rozmawiali o jakejs umowie o dzielo, i planie przejecia prawowitego spadku. Nie pamietam z tego za wiele, bo bylem wtedy maly i nie rozumialem wszytkich slow. Potem wypili po maluchu, i wyruszyli w {droge}.",
	["From my father's {letters}, I learned that while traveling, they were accompanied by music. He wrote that the melody and vocals came from behind the screen, whatever that means. On the seventh day of the journey, when they decided to set up camp and go to sleep, something unexpected happened. Three sopranist Januses started singing: 'Memento mori es grande finali. Burn their bodies in our dark rally' and then they broke the fourth wall. While revealing their vile faces and they captured the adventurers. Then, fat Janus the Baritone (a hater of all changes, like compulsory zipper merging), turned the tide of action. While simultaneously addressing all the heroes of all times in all of the universe's history, he uttered these words: 'PRICKS' fat Janus the baritone roasted the vile sopranists in the embers of Polish hatred, and then he returned to Olympus. With his departure, Gruby Janusz left behind a map of Poland's roads. Since then, I haven't heard any mention of the Janus choir."] = "Z {listow} Ojca wynika, ze w czasie ich wedrowki towarzyszyla im muzyka. Pisal, ze melodia i wokale wydobywaja sie zza ekranu, cokolwiek to znaczy. Siodemego dnia wyprawy, gdy postanowili, ze rozbija oboz i pojda spac, stalo sie cos nieoczekiwanego. Trzech januszy-sopranistow zaczelo spiewac: 'Memento mori es grande finali. Dawaj ich janusz do mikrofali', a nastepnie zlamalo czwarta sciane i zlapalo bohaterow w niewole, ujawniajac swe plugawe oblicza. Wtem Gruby Janusz - basista, dokonal zwrotu akcji. Jednoczesnie przemawiajac do wszystkich bohaterow wszelkiej literatury w historii wszechswiata, wypowiada te slowa: CHUJE. Gruby Janusz - basista (nienawistnik wszelkich zmian, takich jak przymus jazdy na suwak) piecze plugawych sopranistow w ogniu polskiej nienawisci, po czym wraca na olimp. Wraz z swoim odejsciem, Gruby Janusz zostawia za soba mape samochodowa polski. Od tamtego momentu nie slyszalem juz zadnych wzmianek o chorze januszy.",
	["From the most {recent} letters, I learned that they fought with mutts, homeless people, and other abominations in the hundred-mile forest. That was still within the borders of our Voivodeship. They reached the northern edge of the familiar territory, and just by the scent of the air, they knew that in this part of the country, people lived at least as well as the homeless in Hurghada. Being abroad, they were invited to a dinner (out of pity) by a camel farm owner. Then, they went to bed, I don't know where."] = "Z najbardziej {aktualnych} listow dowiedzialem sie, ze na wysokosci stumilowego lasu walczyli z kundlami, bezdomnymi i innymi poczwarami. A to wszystko bylo jeszcze w granicach wojewodztwa Podlaskiego. Dotarli na polnocny skraj dobrze znanej sobie krainy i juz po samym zapachu powietrza wiedzieli, ze w tej czesci kraju ludziom zyje sie co najmniej tak dobrze, jak bezdomnym w Hurghadzie. Bedac za granica zostali zaproszeni na obiad przez bogatego prywaciarza z domku jednorodzinnego (z litosci). A potem polezli chuj wie gdzie.",
	["Three months have passed since the last letter, and I used to receive them at monthly intervals. That's why I got worried about their current condition. I can't leave my kingdom, but if you're determined, I can help you find them. Let me know when you're {ready}. In the meantime, I'll try to estimate their last location and possible direction."] = "Od ostatniego listu minely 3 miesiace, a poprzednie dostawalem w interwalach najwyzej miesiecznych. Stad zaniepokoilem sie stanem ich kompanii. Ja nie moge opuszczac mojego krolestwa, ale jezeli jestes zdecydowany, to moge Ci pomoc ich odszukac. Daj mi znac, kiedy bedziesz {gotowy}. Ja w tym czasie sproboje przygotowac estymacje ich ostatniego miejsca pobytu oraz mozliwy dalszy kierunek.",
	["I've placed their possible location in your quest log. Good luck. And as for the Janusz choir... aside from that, people. I can lend you my scroll with various poems. Oh, and one more thing. Based on my estimates, the company may have passed near Goldblum's burrow. He's known for posing very difficult riddles, and failing to solve them ends, the very least, badly. You might want to go to someone who's escaped his clutches before - Far Myrrus."] = "Zamiescilem ich mozliwa lokacje w twoim quest logu. Powodzenia. A co do choru januszy... oprocz tego ludzie. Moge Ci uzyczyc mojego kajetu z roznymi poematami. Aha, i jeszce jedna rzecz. Z moich szacowan wynika, ze kompania mogla przechodzic niedaleko nory {Goldbluma}. Jest on znany z zadawania bardzo trudnych zagadek, ktorych nierozwiazanie konczy sie lepiej nie mowic czym. Mozesz udac sie najpierw do kogos, kto juz raz ponoc wydostal sie z jego szponow - Gruby Mirek.",
	["Seriusly, talk to Far Myrrus about Goldblum."] = "Mowie Ci, zapytaj Grubego Mirka o Goldbluma.",
	["I have bad news. The stress level of the Rat of Kings reached the maximum possible value upon hearing about the Passat wreckage. Rats, unlike humans, react differently to such circumstances. Their reaction is self-destruction of the organism and tearing the soul into billions of smaller rat souls and Schrodinger's souls, each existing and not existing at the same time. The only way to bring him back to life is to find all the Schr√∂dinger's souls and separate them from the real rat ones. Leave this problem to me, as I need you for another {task}."] = "Mam zle wiesci. Poziom stresu Szczura Krolow urosl do maksymalnej mozliwej wartosci na wiesc o rozwalonych passatach. Szczury, w odroznieniu od ludzi, inaczej reaguja na takie okolicznosci. U nich reakcja jest autodestrukcja organizmu i rozerwanie duszy na miliardy mniejszych dusz szczurzych i dusz shroedingera, z ktorych kazda istnieje i nie istnieje jednoczesnie. Jedynym sposobem na przywrocenie go do zycia jest odnalezienei wszystkich dusz shoredingera i odsepwarowane ich od tych prawdziwych, szczurzych. Ten problem jednak zostaw mi, gdyz Tobie musze powierzyc aktualnie inne {zadanie}.",
	["What are you doing in my kosher cave? And you know what, I only have two entrances here: one normal and one through the toilet. I can smell which one you used, you pig."] = "Co wy robita w mojej koszernej pieczarze? I wiesz co, prowadzo tu tylko dwa wejscia: jedno normalne, drugie przez kibel. I czuje przez ktore zes wlozl, swinio.",
	["I'm Goldblum, and I feel like you'll want something from me that I won't want to give. Like money, for example. Or maybe you need {help}?"] = "Jestem Goldblum i czuje, ze byndziesz cos ode mnie chciol, na co nie bynde mial ochoty. Jak na przyklod syks za piniondze. A moze potrzebujesz stad {wyjsc}?",
	["Alright, but you have to answer my {riddle}. Then I'll answer yours. If you lose, it's sex for money without money."] = "Dobra, ale musita odpowiedziec na mojo {zagodke}. Potem ja na twojo. Jak przegrosz byndzie seks za piniondze bez piniendzy.",
	["What determines the valuation of structured bonds, index certificates, participation certificates, and other structured products, you school-less wretch?"] = "Od czego zalezy wycena obligacji strukturyzowanych, certyfikatow indeksowych, certyfikatow partycypacyjnych i innych produktow strukturyzowanych, gnoju bez szkoly?",
	["CUT THE CRAP! HOW DID YOU KNOW, YOU STUPID IDIOT!! Never mind. Ask your question - there's no question that will surprise my devious, vile mind."] = "KURWA SKADZES WIEDZIOL GLUPI GNOJU!! Niewazne. Wal zagadke - nie ma pytanka, na ktorym bys zaskoczyl moj podstepny umys parszywcu.",
	["So, give me the ryddle!"] = "No dawaj te zagadke!",
	["SHIT, because YOU'RE BROKE! No? How can that be? You're not welcome here anymore. Others like you went through that wire, and I showed them the way to the hive. Farewell, scoundrel."] = "Gowno, bos biedak! Jak to zle? Tys juz tu nie jest myle wydziony. Inni tacy jak Ty wyszli tamtym wirem i wskazalem im droge do hive. Zegnam oziemble.",
	["No, no... now lets commence six for money. *licks his lips*"] = "Oj nie, teraz nedzoe syks za piniondze. *mlask*",
	["What are you trying? Answer immediately!"] = "Co ty tu robisz? Natychmiast odpowiadaj",
	["Come back with two dragon porkcuts, and I promise I'll help you."] = "Wroc z dwoma schabozadami, a obiecuje, ze Ci pomoge.",
	["I know where you can find your friends. But first, I expect something in return. Bring me two dragon porkcuts, and I'll help you."] = "Wiem gdzie mozesz znalesc swoich przyjaciol. Jednak najpierw oczekuje czegos w zamian. Przynies mi dwa smocze schabozady, a Ci pomoge.",
	["Your party went to the only source of pure water - the abandoned shack on the Wyvern Hill."] = "Twoja kompania udala sie do jedynego darmowego zrodla czystej wody - opuszczona chata na wzgorzu wyvern.",
	["I've been visited before by those who asked, 'spare any help, boss?' If you renovate my old town, we'll consider it. You can also bring me a crystal of the depths. Do one of these, and I'll surely reward you."] = "Juz raz byli tu tacy co pytali 'Pomozesz, kierowniku?'. Jezeli odremontujesz mi starowke, to pomyslimy. Mozesz tez przyniesc mi krysztal glebinowy. Zrob jedna z tych rzeczy, a na pewno sie odwdziecze.",
	["What you're looking for is in the lizardmen village. The lizardmen stumbled upon underground bug light deposits, and now they're exploiting them to the max. However, they stumbled upon something much more powerful - an ancient artifact. My scouts told me they guard it like a treasure it is. They recently moved it to the highest tower."] = "To czego szukasz znajduje sie w wiosce jaszczuroludzi. Jasczuroludzie natrafili na podziemne zloza harnasi, i teraz na potege je eksploatuja. Trafili jednak na cos o wiele bardziej potezniejszego - pradawny artefakt. Moi zwiadowcy przekazali mi, ze strzega tego jak oczka w glowie. Ostatnio przeniesli go do najwyzszej wiezy.",
	["If you don't know where to find the crystals, try diving into the sea east of here."] = "Jezeli nie wiesz gdzie znalezc krysztaly, to sproboj zanurkowac w morzu na wschod stad.",
	["Don't wait for the sramatians. They're slacking on purpose to avoid having to fight {HF-P/X}. Besides, do you have all the {runes}?"] = "Nie czekaj na sramatow. Specjalnie slackuja, zeby nie musiec walczyc z {HF-P/X}. Poza tym, masz jusz wszystie {runy}?",
	["While you were traveling the world, I went to the library in Zbaszyn. I found information that HF-P/X terrorized an ancient temple where the treasury of Passats was located. For uncounted years, it's been hiding somewhere in the underground of that temple. I think he might want to use Passats in a fight. Perhaps he possesses necromantic abilities and can animate inanimate objects. Or maybe he'll use Passats as kamikaze projectiles? Don't wait for the sramats; they won't come."] = "W czasie, gdy wy wedrowaliscie po swiecie, ja udalem sie do biblioteki w zbaszynku. Znalazlem tam informacje, ze HF-P/X zterroryzowal pradawna swiatynie, w ktorej znajdowal sie skarbiec passatow. Od niepamietnych czasow ukrywa sie gdzies wsrod podziemii tej swiatyni. Mysle, ze bedzie mogl chciec uzyc passatow do walki. Byc moze posiada umiejtnosci nekromanty i potrafi animowac przedmioty nieozywione. A byc moze uzyje passatow jako pociskow kamikaze? Nie czekaj na sramatow, oni nie przyjda.",
	["Yes, those are all the needed runes. You can now try to use the enchanted lever. Maybe we'll find HF-P/X here."] = "Tak, to wszystkie potrzebne runy. Mozesz teraz sprobowac uzyc zakletej dzwigni. Byc moze znajdziemy tu HF-P/X.",
	["I see you don't have all the runes yet."] = "Widze, ze nie masz jeszcze wszystkich run.",
	["WHAAAAAT??? How many Passats were lost there? I'm about to faint..."] = "Cooooo??? Ile passatow tam zginelo? Chyba zaraz zemdleje....",
	["I'm gonna stay here and have your back."] = "Ja zostane tutaj. Bede cie ubezpieczal.",
	["Pirate rum. Bilbeus might be interested in this one"] = "Piracki rum. Bilbeusz moze byc nim zainteresowany.",
	["Unsealing rune"] = "Runa odpieczetowujaca",
	["Deep sea crystal"] = "Krysztal glebinowy",
	["Your team left me a note stating they headed to the desert. You can ask Jannah'ma for help finding them."] = "Twoja druzyna udala sie w strone pustyni. Sproboj spytac Jannah'ma, byc moze bedzie we stanie ci pomoc.",
}
